\begin_layout Standard
The Rabbit's Nest certainly looked impressive, even though it was in effect
 nothing more then a really deep and monstrously wide underground well.
 There were actually buildings sitting atop those balconies, as well as
 blast-proof doors scattered around the rock walls, large and small.
 There were all sorts of weird-looking people giving me the eye for no obvious
 reason, perhaps apart from the fact that I had this very miserable looking
 face on, feeling groggy, famished, and probably unable to resist the urge
 to use the bathroom pretty soon as well.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I didn't bother returning those looks, even though I felt I had every right
 to do so because of the silly hat, which Steve had so many times bothered
 to correct me on every occasion was called a mitre, and kept reminding
